This game is really fun yet difficult, which provides a good balance. The planes are very creative. There is, however, one thing I have a problem with. There seems to be a lot of Satanic planes in both versions of the game. First off, you have planes that feature a Pentagram as the emblem on their wings. Second, some of the names of the planes are a bit concerning too. Two of the planes are named Satanael and Beelzebub. 

If it weren't for those facts, this app would have gotten a 5 star review from me. Sorry!

I loved this the instant I lay my hands on it. It's fun, it's easy to pick up and the humor is just excellent. This game has cartoon dogfights the way they should be. 
I have just one suggestion: more players on local matches. I have a handful of friends that enjoy casual multiplayer games. We were delighted with games such as multipong on the iPad, or Super stickman golf, but truth be told, they got boring. 
So I wanted to introduce Mini Squadron to them, but noticed that the bluetooth multiplayer can only support 2. Wouldn't there be  more mayhem with more players?

Thanks for the wonderful game,

Really a fun game. Controls are good, and it's easy to figure out. But the big issues have to do with the planes themselves.  First off you unlock netter planes by getting really high scores. However, if you keep progressing with low scores, an bad planes, you can't really get better ones because you keep getting killed. Second, the animal planes that are piloted by the games AI have way to much speed. Basically, they are really slow if you use them, but are fast if they are against you. Regardless, I highly recommend this game.

Simply a game I didn't expect to keep playing after dying so many times. 

The way to unlock new planes is interesting because you won't be able to unlock all the planes until you get really good...... It took me three hours to get good enough but it was worth it when I unlocked the "singularity" ship and after that everything was a LOT easier.

Overall a great game for something I got for free. So definitely worth the $1 price tag.
